DefectDescribe.Content:
Crack -- One or more of the following conditions exist:
                        1) fine cracks are visible on the pipe wall;
                        2) A small amount of sediment is generated from the cracks on thepipe wall;
                        3) Mild peeling.

Collapse--One or more of the following conditions exist:
                       1) The circumferential coverage of the crack, crack or broken edge of the pipe material is greater than the arc length of 60°;
                       2) The circumferential extent of the wall material falling off is greater than the arc length of 60°.
